items: Short list of topics of interest:
• Strategies for bias detection and mitigation in LLM outputs.
• Frameworks for enhancing the explainability and transparency of Large Language Models.
• Ethical data curation practices for training Large Language Models.
• Governance frameworks for Responsible Artificial Intelligence in the context of LLM deployment.
• Techniques for real-time processing and concurrency in Large Language Models.
• Case studies on the societal impact of LLMs and ethical implications of their use.
• Participatory approaches to AI governance involving multiple stakeholders.
•  Methods for auditing and refining Large Language Models post-deployment.
• User privacy considerations in the development and deployment of LLMs.
1. Quality and originality in theory and methodology of the special issue.
